==English==

{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From French [[muscle#French|muscle]], from Latin [[musculus]], literally ‘little mouse’ (from the mouselike appearence of some muscles).

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈmʌsəl/}}
*mŭsʹəl, /<tt>"mVs@l</tt>/
:*Homophones: [[mussel]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[contractile]] form of [[tissue]] which [[animal]]s use to effect movement.
# An [[organ]] composed of muscle tissue.
#(''figurative'') [[Strength]].

